f of guinea and atlantic ocean in the south a multicultural nation ghana has a population of approximately  million spanning a variety of ethnic linguistic and religious groups five percent of the population practices traditional faiths  adhere to christianity and  are muslim its diverse geography and ecology ranges from coastal savannahs to tropical jungles ghana is a democratic country led by a president who is both head of state and head of the government ghanas economy is one of the strongest and most diversified in africa following a quarter century of relative stability and good governance ghanas growing economic prosperity and democratic political system have made it a regional power in west africa notable firmsedit this list includes notable companies with primary headquarters located in the country the industry and sector follow the industry classification benchmark taxonomy organizations which have ceased operations are included and noted as defunct      active firms      stateowned firms      defunct firms name industry sector headquarters founded notes accra brewery company consumer goods food  beverage accra  brewery gse abl aerogem aviation industrials industrial transportation accra  cargo airline afra airlines consumer services travel  leisure accra  airline defunct  africa world airlines consumer services travel  leisure accra  airline african champion industries basic materials basic resources accra 9 paper gse aci agricultural development bank of ghana financials banks accra  commercial bank aluworks industrials general industries accra 9 aluminiumbased products gse alw amalbank financials banks accra 99 commercial bank antrak air consumer services travel  leisure accra  airline ashanti goldfields corporation basic materials basic resources obuasi 9 gold mining merged into anglogold ashanti south africa ayrton drugs health care pharmaceuticals accra  pharmaceutical gse ayrtn bank of africa ghana limited financials banks accra 99 commercial bank ba